  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6934 sitting between the flip (6857) and major resistance wall at 6950 (+16.2B GEX), dealers are in active selling mode as they hedge their long gamma positions against the recent 1.1% 5-minute rally. The PIN regime and massive positive gamma concentration from 6900-7000 creates a strong magnetic pull that should cap upside momentum and trigger mean reversion selling pressure as spot approaches the 6950 wall. Watch for dealers to aggressively sell any push toward 6950-7000, while 6900 support and the 6857 flip level become key downside pivots where buying interest should emerge.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to get rejected at 6950 and chop sideways between 6900-6950.",
